briefdescription.para: LNS heuristic that finds the optimal rounding to a given point.

detaileddescription.para: Timo Berthold RENS is a large neighborhood search start heuristic, i.e., unlike other LNS heuristics, it does not need a known feasible solution. It solves a sub-SCIP that is created by fixing variables which take an integral value in a given LP or NLP solution. For the remaining integer variables, the bounds get tightened to the two nearest integral values.
